[I take responsibility for posting these messages. The latter sounds as
much political as medical. My reason for posting this is to point out how
sensitized politicians are, and how easily people blame governments for
occurrences no one could reasonably avoid. On the other hand, this message
also is instructive in that the Hong Kong authorities are saying the strain
of EV-71 currently circulating there is "not deadly" and there is "no
evidence of mutation". I take this to indicate the Hong Kong strain is
different from the Malaysian and Taiwanese strains. Of course, other
answers could be that insufficient strain characterization has been done in
Hong Kong or that the epidemiologic situation in Hong Kong is different
from those in Malaysia and Taiwan, i.e., the still-undefined second agent
has not been found in Hong Kong. As Yogi Berra said, "It ain't over until
it's over." (For those of you unfamiliar with U.S. philosophers, Yogi Berra
is not one of them.) - Mod.CHC ................................chc/es
